12. Shielding Responsibilities (Indemnity):

In the event that any claim, loss, damage, or expense (including reasonable attorney's fees) arises out of or in connection with this Agreement, the indemnifying Party shall have the right to be fully compensated and defended by the indemnified Party. This defense and indemnification obligation will not apply unless the claim, loss, damage, or expense results from:

a) The indemnifying Party's gross negligence;
b) The indemnifying Party's intentional misconduct;
c) A breach of this Agreement by the indemnified Party.

In other words, while the original clause placed the responsibility primarily on the indemnifier, this revised version shifts some of that responsibility back to the indemnified Party, specifically for claims resulting from gross negligence or intentional misconduct by the indemnifying Party, as well as breaches of the Agreement by the indemnified Party.
